ğŸ“Œ C programming mein functions ek block of code hai jo aapke program mein ek special task ko execute karta hai. Functions ka use aapko code ko modular aur organized banane mein help karta hai.

ğŸ“Œ Functions ke 3 main parts hai:

ğŸ“ 1: Return Type: Function ke return type us type ka variable hota hai jo function apne call karne wale part ko back karne ke liye use karta hai. Agar function ko koi value back nahi karna hai to return type 'void' hota hai.

ğŸ“ 2: Function Name: Function ka name aap apne hisab se decide kar sakte hai, lekin iska use function ko call karne ke liye karna hoga.

ğŸ“ 3: Parameters: Parameters function ko call karne wale part se data pass karna hai function ko, isliye function ko ek list of parameters diye jate hai jo function ko use karna hai.

Example:

#include <stdio.h>
int add(int a, int b) {
    return a + b;
}

int main() {
    int sum = add(2, 3);
    printf("The result is %d\n", sum);
    return 0;
}

ğŸ“Œ Is example mein, 'add' function ke return type int hota hai aur ismein 2 integers diye gaye hai parameters. 'add' function ka use main function mein kiya gaya hai aur ismein 2 aur 3 diye gaye hai parameters. 'add' function call ke baad, iska result '5' hai jo main function mein 'sum' variable mein save kiya gaya hai.

ğŸ“Œ Functions ke use aapko code ko modular aur organized banane mein help karta hai aur code ka reuse bhi ho jata hai. Agar aap ek function ka use repeat karne ki jarurat hai, to aap usko ek baar define karke, repeatedly use kar sakte hai.

ğŸ“Œ Functions ke some important rules:

ğŸ“ 1: Function ke return type aur name ke alawa, function ke parameters bhi decide karte hai.

ğŸ“ 2: Function ko define karne ke baad, call kar sakte hai.

ğŸ“ 3: Function ke scope ko define karne ke liye function ke alawa, aapke program mein function declaration bhi laga sakte hai.

ğŸ“ 4: Function ko recursive (self-calling) bhi banaya jata hai.

ğŸ“Œ Parameterized functions C programming mein functions hai jo kuch parameters lete hain jinse unki functionality decide ki ja sakti hai. Parameters function ko call karne wale part se data pass karna hai, isliye function ko ek list of parameters diye jate hai jo function ko use karna hai.

