ğŸ“Œ C programming mein functions ke parameters pass karne ke do tarah hoti hai: Call By Value aur Call By Reference.

ğŸ“Œ Call By Value: Call By Value mein, function ke parameters ko pass karne ke liye, copy of actual parameter ke values pass hote hai. Isliye, agar function mein any changes kar liye jate hai, to actual parameter ke values mein koi changes nahi hoti. Call By Value ka use generally small data types ke liye hota hai.

ğŸ“Œ Call By Reference: Call By Reference mein, function ke parameters ko pass karne ke liye, actual parameter ke addresses pass hote hai. Isliye, agar function mein any changes kar liye jate hai, to actual parameter ke values mein bhi changes hoti hai. Call By Reference ka use generally complex data types ke liye hota hai.

Example:

#include <stdio.h>

void swapByValue(int a, int b) {
    int temp = a;
    a = b;
    b = temp;
}

void swapByReference(int *a, int *b) {
    int temp = *a;
    *a = *b;
    *b = temp;
}

int main() {
    int num1 = 5, num2 = 10;

    printf("Before swapping: num1 = %d, num2 = %d\n", num1, num2);

    swapByValue(num1, num2);
    printf("After swapping by value: num1 = %d, num2 = %d\n", num1, num2);

    swapByReference(&num1, &num2);
    printf("After swapping by reference: num1 = %d, num2 = %d\n", num1, num2);

    return 0;
}

ğŸ“Œ Is example mein, 'swapByValue' function Call By Value ka use kar rakha hai aur 'swapByReference' function Call By Reference ka use kar rakha hai. 'swapByValue' function mein, num1 aur num2 ke copy pass hote hai aur ismein koi changes nahi hoti. 'swapByReference' function mein, num1 aur num2 ke addresses pass hote hai aur ismein actual values mein bhi changes hoti hai.

ğŸ“Œ Call By Value aur Call By Reference ke use se aapko code ko modular aur organized banane mein help karta hai aur code ka reuse bhi ho jata hai. Agar aap ek function ka use repeat karne ki jarurat hai, to aap usko ek baar define karke, repeatedly use kar sakte hai.

ğŸ“Œ Call By Value aur Call By Reference ke some important rules:

ğŸ“ 1: Call By Value mein, function ke parameters ko pass karne ke liye, copy of actual parameter ke values pass hote hai.

ğŸ“ 2: Call By Reference mein, function ke parameters ko pass karne ke liye, actual parameter ke addresses pass hote hai.

ğŸ“ 3: Call By Value ka use generally small data types ke liye hota hai.

ğŸ“ 4: Call By Reference ka use generally complex data types ke liye hota hai.

ğŸ“ 5: Call By Value mein, actual parameter ke values mein koi changes nahi hoti.

ğŸ“ 6: Call By Reference mein, actual parameter ke values mein bhi changes hoti hai.

ğŸ“Œ C programming mein, structure ek user-defined data type hai jo multiple variables ko ek sath rakhta hai. Isse, aap ek single entity mein multiple data types ke variables ko store kar sakte hai. Structure ke variables ko fields ya members kehte hai.

Example:

#include <stdio.h>

struct Employee {
