ğŸ“ 5: Structure ka size determined nahi hota hai, isliye ek structure ko another structure ke part naheen banaya jaa sakta.

ğŸ“ 6: Structure ko define karne ke baad, use karne ke liye ek object banaai jati hai aur ismein fields mein data store karte hai.

ğŸ“Œ Structure ke use se aapko code ko modular aur organized banane mein help karta hai aur code ka reuse bhi ho jata hai. Agar aap ek structure ka use repeat karne ki jarurat hai, to aap usko ek baar define karke, repeatedly use kar sakte hai.

ğŸ“Œ C programming mein, pointer ek variable hai jo baad mein memory ke address ko store kar sakte hai. Pointers ke use se aapko memory ke direct manipulation karne mein help karta hai.

Example:

#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int a = 10;
    int *p;

    p = &a; // Pointer ke address mein variable ke address ko store kar diya gaya hai

    printf("Value of a: %d\n", a);
