    printf("Value of p: %p\n", p);

    return 0;
}

ğŸ“Œ Is example mein, 'a' variable ke address ko pointer variable 'p' mein store kar diya gaya hai. Pointer variable 'p' ko use karke, aap 'a' variable ke value ko direct get sakte hai.

ğŸ“Œ Pointers ke some important features:

ğŸ“ 1: Pointer variable ko declare karne ke baad, memory ko allocate nahi hota hai.

ğŸ“ 2: Pointer variable ko use karke, aap memory ke direct manipulation kar sakte hai.

ğŸ“ 3: Pointer variable ko declare karne ke baad, use karne ke liye ek variable banaai jati hai.

ğŸ“ 4: Pointer variable ko use karke, aap memory ke direct manipulation kar sakte hai.

ğŸ“ 5: Pointer variable ko use karne ke baad, use karne ke liye ek variable banaai jati hai.

ğŸ“ 6: Pointer variable ko use karne ke baad, use karne ke liye ek variable banaai jati hai aur ismein memory ke address ko store kar diya gaya hai.

ğŸ“Œ Pointers ke use se aapko code ko modular aur organized banane mein help karta hai aur code ka reuse bhi ho jata hai. Agar aap ek pointer ka use repeat karne ki jarurat hai, to aap usko ek baar define karke, repeatedly use kar sakte hai.

Pointers ke use se aapko C programming mein code likhne ka aur debug karne ka maza aata hai.

